remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` encodes pixel data into WebP format, supporting both single-frame (static) and multi-frame (animated) WebP files. Pass an <see cref="T:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions" /> to control quality, compression, and animation settings.

For animated WebP, build a sequence of <see cref="T:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame" /> objects — each wrapping a bitmap/image/pixmap with a frame duration — and pass the span to one of the `EncodeAnimated` overloads.

## Examples

```csharp
// Encode a single frame to WebP
using var bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode("input.png");
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());

// Encode an animated WebP
var frames = new[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
};
using var animData = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, options);
```
